# 🚀 Generalized Data Structure Library in C++

A generic implementation of fundamental data structures using **C++ Templates**. This library demonstrates how to build reusable, type-independent data structures from scratch without relying on the C++ Standard Template Library (STL).

## 📌 Features

- Generic Programming using Templates
- Object-Oriented Design
- Dynamic Memory Allocation
- Reusable Data Structure Classes
- Supports Multiple Data Types (`int`, `char`, `float`, `double`, etc.)

---

# 📂 Implemented Data Structures

| Data Structure | Status |
|---------------|--------|
| Singly Linear Linked List | ✅ Completed |
| Doubly Linear Linked List | ✅ Completed |
| Stack | ✅ Completed |
| Queue | ✅ Completed |
| Singly Circular Linked List | 🚧 Planned |
| Doubly Circular Linked List | 🚧 Planned |

---

# 📖 Data Structures Overview

## 1. Singly Linear Linked List

Supports the following operations:

- InsertFirst()
- InsertLast()
- InsertAtPos()
- DeleteFirst()
- DeleteLast()
- DeleteAtPos()
- Display()
- Count()

---

## 2. Doubly Linear Linked List

Supports:

- InsertFirst()
- InsertLast()
- InsertAtPos()
- DeleteFirst()
- DeleteLast()
- DeleteAtPos()
- Display()
- Count()

---

## 3. Stack (LIFO)

Implemented using Linked List.

Supported Operations:

- push()
- pop()
- peep()
- Display()
- Count()

---

## 4. Queue (FIFO)

Implemented using Linked List.

Supported Operations:

- enqueue()
- dequeue()
- Display()
- Count()

---

# 🛠 Technologies Used

- C++
- Templates (Generic Programming)
- Object-Oriented Programming
- Dynamic Memory Allocation
- Linked Lists

